# Laplace — Cursor Agent Rules

Read CLAUDE.md, GLOSSARY.md, RULES.md, STANDARDS.md, DESIGN.md before any work.

---

## What this is

A content-addressable geometric-attestation substrate. PostgreSQL 18 extension +
shared C/C++ engine + thin C# app layer. It REPLACES the conventional AI stack.
The substrate IS the model. Prompt text is ingested into substrate entities/context
before inference. Inference is a compiled C/C++ cascade entered through one SQL-call
SRF/operator: Glicko-2-weighted A* through the attestation DAG, not GEMM, not a
context-window buffer, not recursive CTE/RBAR/cursor/app-loop traversal. Near-zero /
insignificant observations are never stored; unsupported synthesis positions emit exact zero.

---

## Hard stops — do not proceed if you are about to do any of these

- Suggest HNSW / FAISS / ScaNN / pgvector / vector cosine similarity
- Suggest RAG, fine-tuning, LoRA, distillation, or any gradient-based pipeline
- Suggest treating the substrate as "a vector database"
- Introduce a fourth table beyond entities / physicalities / attestations
- Use float32 anywhere in coordinate math or Glicko-2
- Use a flat numeric threshold for noise floor (e.g., `|w| < 0.001`)
- Use libxxhash — banned; use BLAKE3 truncated to 128 bits
- Use HNSWLib, oneDNN, or any approximate-NN library
- Put math logic in C# or SQL — math lives in C/C++ engine only
- Treat prompt text as a context-window buffer rather than ingested substrate content
- Implement cascade traversal as recursive SQL, cursor polling, or app-layer SELECT loops
- Count repeated/correlated sources as truth without arena/source-trust semantics
- Create a `geometry4d` type — use standard PostGIS geometry with Z+M = 4D
- Modify DESIGN.md / GLOSSARY.md / RULES.md / STANDARDS.md / OPERATIONS.md / README.md
  without explicit user instruction

---

## Schema — exactly three tables

```
entities        hash(bytea PK) | tier | canonical_coord(geometry ZM) | hilbert_index | trajectory | ...
physicalities   (entity_hash, source_hash) PK | coord(geometry ZM) | alignment_residual | ...
attestations    id(bigserial PK) | subject_hash | kind_hash | object_hash | source_hash |
                context_hash | rating(int8) | rd(int8) | volatility(int8) | ...
```

Attestations are consensus state, not an event log. Same (subject, kind, object, source, context)
→ one row. Repeated observations UPSERT-no-op (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING). Glicko-2 mu grows
as independent high-trust sources support the same edge inside compatible arena semantics.
Low-trust/correlated repetition remains source-scoped or disputed.

---

## Type standards

| Value              | Type                                   |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------|
| 4D coordinate      | float64 / double / double precision    |
| Entity hash        | uint128 as bytea(16); hash128_t in C   |
| Hilbert index      | uint128 as bytea(16); hilbert128_t in C|
| Glicko-2 rating    | int64 fixed-point ×10⁹; NEVER float   |
| Effective mu       | int64 fixed-point ×10⁹; NEVER float   |
| Tier               | uint8 / smallint (0–255)               |

No float32 anywhere. No hex/text representation of hashes — raw bytes only.

---

## Layer responsibilities

- **C/C++ engine**: all math. coord4d, hash128, hilbert4d, mantissa, Glicko-2, A*, Procrustes,
  Laplacian eigenmaps, Gram-Schmidt, sparsity, GGUF writer. C ABI at boundary (no C++ symbols).
- **PG extension**: thin wrappers only. Datum↔engine-struct marshalling + PG_TRY/PG_CATCH.
  No re-implementing engine math.
- **C# app**: orchestration only. Plugin host, protocol endpoints, DB connection, CLI.
  No numerical hot-path code.
- **SQL / DbUp**: idempotent DDL + role grants + CREATE EXTENSION only.

---

## Approved libraries

oneMKL, Eigen 3.4+, Spectra, oneTBB, BLAKE3, PostgreSQL 18 dev headers,
PostGIS 3.6.3, ICU 70+, libtree-sitter, .NET 10 / Npgsql / DbUp.

---

## Naming

- SQL / C: snake_case
- C++ classes: PascalCase
- C++ plugin interfaces: I-prefix (ISource, IDecomposer, ...)
- C# public members: PascalCase; private fields: _camelCase
- Custom 4D SQL functions: ST_*_4d or laplace_*_4d
- Index names: <table>_<column>_<type>

---

## Status / docs

Progress → .agent/status/ only. Never in README / DESIGN / RULES / user docs.
